    "original_title": "Brooklyn: Flatbush Avenue - Avenue U",
    "text": "(1) Flatbush Ave., (right) south of Ave. U to Rockaway Inlet, showing a pier at the foot of Flatbush Ave. under construction. Mill Basin is at the left. May 12, 1922. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.\n\n(2) The same, from another angle. The first pier on Jamaica Bay was opened for business on June 1, 1898. August 1925. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.\n\n(3) The same, another angle, showing Mill Basin and Mill Island on the left. August 1925. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.\n\n(4) The same, viewed north, showing Mill Basin. Flatbush Ave. is in the background with raised wires thereon. August 1925. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.\n",
